response.answer_text: Qualcomm Snapdragon 660. ... Announced in mid 2017, the SD660 is the successor to the Snapdragon 625. It features 8 Kryo 260 cores (custom design, 64-Bit capable) that are divided in two clusters. A fast cluster of four cores with up to 2.2 GHz and a power saving efficiency cluster with up to 1.8 GHz. Starting with the Snapdragon 660, the chip is based on 14nm fabrication process and comes with the CPU clock speed ranging from 1.95 GHz to 2.2 GHz. The octa-core silicon features a 64-bit Qualcomm Kryo 260 CPU coupled with Snapdragon X12 LTE modem
